I believe the Mafia team is composed of Ngekop, Kirin, and possibly Sam as well. This is due to numberous reasons, including but not limited to strange interactions, and plain logical reasoning. I have concluded that Kirin is a good lynch for information today. Originally, I wanted to just create "pressure to start the game" (ne27-chat, Hyancith, 11:05 AM PST) and "[generate] some content for day 1" (11:08 AM PST). Note that Ngekop appeared to try and dissuade me from this, and I responded that "it is [just] how I play." (11:13 AM PST). Kirin's reactions following my vote did cause me to start to consider leaving a vote on them, such as their weird justifications for why I am supposedly a Mafia member "since [I couldn't] explain, [I am] probably... mafia." (kirin yang, 11:19 AM PST). Additionally, a major point I will use to argue is the interaction between Kirin and Ngekop when Kirin mentioned not reading his rolecard. Personally, I replied with a mostly generic response to see what would happen. However, Ngekop noticeably was concerned; not only did they try to convey the message that it was a bad idea through possibly "[voting Kirin] and tab for the rest of d1" (Ngekop, 11:12 AM PST), but also yet again tried to subtly tell Kirin to look at their rolecard, by asking "Kirin you already saw your card right?" (11:32 AM PST). On its own, you can likely excuse this as a Town being concerned, but keep this point in mind what I am saying is in brief, Ngekop is teammates with Kirin and worried they didn't look.
17:17
Kirin understandably votes for Ngekop. However, they seem to go through a revelation shortly afterwards, stating "What the hell (Kirin yang, 11:41 AM PST) - and another statement - and unvote. At this point, I state the opposite of what I am thinking, and tell Kirin that they likely did not look at their rolecard for a reason that doesn't really make much sense; "Had you not actually seen your rolecard, you wouldn't have said that in chat." (Hyancith, 11:46 AM PST). This is another reason why I suspect Kirin is paired with Ngekop. As for where Sam fits into this, Ngekop seems to be subtly distancing themselves from Sam while also pairing them with me, claiming that "[I] buddy sam every game" (Ngekop, 12:36 PM PST). Additionally, there was a bit of talk about meta game. So, I took the liberty of looking through some games. Notice how Sam claimed "[they] hate it here" (Sam, 11:38 AM PST) and something similar in the MA43 game "I hate it here" (ma43-chat, Sam, 4:45 AM PST)? He was also Mafia in both games. To be honest, Sam is more only just a scum-lean as compared to Kirin/Ngekop; I'm fine with interchanging a different player in the proposed team, but for the purpose of this essay, he is the one in the team. Ngekop went on an entire tangent about what the PRs should do. You could argue this is behavior of a Town but I will argue back that not only is it the Mafia's job to act like Town, but also that this discussion does not actually give Town credit, rather it is more of a mech discussion. The conclusion you should come to differs really on if the doctor should visit the IC or not. Additionally, this discussion also benefits Mafia!Ngekop, as it helps the Mafia with what exactly PRs are doing. A very minor note of suspicion is also the fact Ngekop was quick to assume that doc and enchantress are in the game; do they know that they are for sure? (This is likely just a coincidence.)
17:17
As mentioned earlier, the conversation is really just mech based. When Dero correctly determined the proper actions (Ngekop also seemed to forget doctor was not consecutive; could this be trying to gain trust?) and also pinged the IC, Ngekop immediately took the opportunity to state that "[they] like dero more now." (ne26-chat, Ngekop, 12:54 AM PST), despite it only being a mech conversation in which Mafia could also point out the same. (This does lead to a slight possibility that Dero could also be a candidate for a Mafia team of Kirin/Ngekop/Dero?) My final point is Ngekop deciding they will supposedly SR me after I point out that Ngekop could be pocketing Dero. While Dero has the Townier response of saying that "not everything going on must be a pocket" (Dero, 12:57 AM PST), Ngekop reacts by placing a vote on me; I was merely voicing the possibility of it being a pocket (in fact, I did not even come on aggressively, I did it indirectly by stating "My brain just screamed "pocket" at me"). When I question them, they essentially accuse me of being a Mafia because I am trying to "copy [my] plays from previous games to resemble townyness" (Ngekop, 1:21 PM PST) and claim it makes no sense that I immediately pointed out a supposed pocket. I see this as a more scum-oriented reaction (as I said, Dero had a Townier response).
17:17
In brief, I strongly believe that Kirin/Ngekop are a possible Mafia pair, with a potential third partner in Sam though this point is weak and interchangeable with other players. Lynching Kirin should be good for information, as it will affect the validity of these reads. If Kirin flips scum, then logically Ngekop should be a good lynch.
